get.description: This endpoint exposes the information related to a customer's sold to account as well as their shipping information (ship to).
get.summary: Returns List of Customer Sold-To Accounts

parameters.name: lastUpdatedDatetimeUtc
parameters.description: Use this query parameter to get a list of soldTo accounts that have been last updated since a specific date time.

parameters.name: branchNumber
parameters.description: Use this parameter to filter soldTos that belong to a particular branchNumber. Branch Number is used to avoid collision between L&W and ABC and POS and Agility **Value should match geography api return value.

parameters.name: identificationCode
parameters.description: Use this parameter to retrieve a soldTo by its unique identifier. One of identificationCode | soldToName | searchQuery is required.

parameters.name: soldToName
parameters.description: Use this parameter to filter soldTos by their name, this supports partial searches. One of identificationCode | soldToName | searchQuery is required.

parameters.name: searchCriteria
parameters.description: Use this parameter as a general search field, this field can search a soldTos name, identificationCode, or phone number. One of identificationCode | soldToName | searchQuery is required.

parameters.name: districtNumber
parameters.description: Use this parameter to filter soldTos by the district that they belong to.

parameters.name: embed
parameters.description: This parameter determines whether the soldTos in the response will include their associated shipTo, billTo, or billingPreferences properties. The input is in string CSV format. If nothing is provided it defaults to not include shipTo or billTo in response payload.

parameters.name: status
parameters.description: Flag to filter accounts by whether they are active or inactive. This API returns active accounts when no status is given.

parameters.name: sellable
parameters.description: Flag to filter accounts by whether they should be sold to or not. This API defaults to sellable true if not provided.

parameters.name: storefront
parameters.description: Flag to filter accounts by the storefront that it belongs to.

200.description: Sold To and a collection of SoldTo Accounts

get.description: This endpoint exposes to whom the product will be shipped to (the ship to) and all of the relevant information related to that account (Billing preferences, address, contact information, etc.)
get.summary: Returns List of Customer Ship-To Accounts

parameters.name: identificationCode
parameters.description: Use this parameter to retrieve a soldTo by its unique identifier. Can be jobAccountNumber or soldToNumber. One of identificationCode | shipToName | searchQuery is required.

parameters.name: shipToName
parameters.description: Use this parameter to filter shipTos by their name, this supports partial searches. One of identificationCode | shipToName | searchQuery is required.

parameters.name: searchCriteria
parameters.description: Use this parameter as a general search field, this field can search a soldTos name, identificationCode, or phone number. One of identificationCode | shipToName | searchQuery is required.

parameters.name: branchNumber
parameters.description: Use this parameter to filter shipTos that belong to a particular branchNumber. The branch number parameter is REQUIRED if identificationCode is not sent in. If identificationCode is present, branch number is not required. Branch Number is used to avoid collision between L&W and ABC and POS and Agility.

parameters.name: districtNumber
parameters.description: Use this parameter to filter shipTos by the district that they belong to.

parameters.name: embed
parameters.description: This parameter determines whether the shipTos in the response will include their associated billTo or billingPreferences properties. The input is in string CSV format. If nothing is provided it defaults to not include billTo or billingPreferences in the response payload.

parameters.name: lastUpdatedDatetimeUtc
parameters.description: Use this query parameter to get a list of shipTo accounts that have been last updated since a specific date time.

parameters.name: status
parameters.description: Flag to filter accounts by whether they are active or inactive. This API returns active accounts when no status is given.

parameters.name: sellable
parameters.description: Flag to filter accounts by whether they should be sold to or not. This API defaults to sellable true if not provided.

parameters.name: storefront
parameters.description: Flag to filter accounts by the storefront that it belongs to.

parameters.name: salesPersonNumber
parameters.description: Sales person number

parameters.name: search
parameters.description: Search salesPersonNumber, salesPersonName or telephone. Wildcard search (at least 3 chars and return http 400 if less than 3 chars provided), case insensitive.

parameters.name: branchNumber
parameters.description: Primary branch number

parameters.name: lastUpdated
parameters.description: Use this query parameter to retrieve information of sales representatives that have been last updated since a specific date time.

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: Page

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: Page size

get.description: The /branches resource allows you to retrieve information about ABC branches. You can filter your result using the several parameters such as storefront, branch number, district number, region number, proximity branch, radius distance from longitude and latitude and user id of the associate with the specific branch responsibilities.

parameters.name: organizationCode
parameters.description: Indicates organization

parameters.name: branchNumber
parameters.description: Either this or branchNumbers (with s) is required.  If both are passed, branchNumber is ignored.

parameters.name: branchNumbers
parameters.description: List of branches delimited by comma (string CSV).  Either this or branchNumber is required.  If both are passed, branchNumber is ignored.

parameters.name: districtNumber
parameters.description: Code identifying the district

parameters.name: regionNumber
parameters.description: Code identifying the region

parameters.name: state
parameters.description: Code identifying the state

parameters.name: openForBusiness
parameters.description: Indication if branch is open to do business

parameters.name: typeCode
parameters.description: Indicates type of branch

parameters.name: latitude
parameters.description: Latitude of branch

parameters.name: longitude
parameters.description: Longitude of branch

parameters.name: radius
parameters.description: Radius search.  Use for searching branches from latitude and longitude

parameters.name: proximityBranch
parameters.description: Code identifying the proximity

parameters.name: userId
parameters.description: Network user name as administered in POS which may be different than Active Directory or Otka. Use to filter branches based on user's responsibilities

parameters.name: select
parameters.description: If this is not passed or if value is 'default', warehouses collections will be included in the return payload.  Also hours collections will be included unless excludeHours=true is passed.

parameters.name: embed
parameters.description: If select query parameter is base (select=base), additional collection of objects will be included in the return payload.  Example embed=warehouses&embed=hours will include warehouses and hours in the payload

parameters.name: excludeHours
parameters.description: true if hours are not desired in the payload. Default is false
